<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1412503" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=621%2C391&#038;ssl=1" alt="Man runs amok in Anambra, kills his 2 children with pestle" width="621" height="391" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=300%2C189&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=1024%2C644&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=768%2C483&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=58%2C36&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=260%2C164&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=200%2C126&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?resize=160%2C100&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?w=1415&amp;ssl=1 1415w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Pestle.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A 34-year old man, Mr. Ifeanyi Apusiobi, from Ogbunike in Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra State, reportedly went berserk, killed his two children with a pestle and used same to inflict injuries on his 72–year-old father. Anambra State Police Public Relations Officer, Mr. Haruna Mohammed, who confirmed the incident, said Apusiobi had been arrested by the police, pending further investigation. According to him, corpses of the children, aged seven and five years, had been deposited at Iyienu Hospital mortuary, Ogidi, for autopsy, while the father of the man who killed his children is receiving treatment at a private hospital. Haruna said: “At about 1a.m., on June 21, police operatives attached to Ogbunike Police Station arrested one Ifeanyi Apusiobi aged 34 years of Azu Ogbunike in Oyi LGA of Anambra State. “The suspect allegedly ran amok under circumstances yet to be ascertained and attacked two of his biological children namely, Chinecherem Apusiobi aged seven years and Obinna Apusiobi aged five years, with a wooden pestle to their heads, while they were sleeping. “He equally used the same object and injured his father, Dominic Apusiobi, aged 72 years, on the head. “Police detectives visited the scene and rushed the victims to the hospital for medical attention, where the two children were certified dead by a medical doctor, while his aged father is responding to treatment” Mohammed added that the police recovered the pestle from the man that killed his children, as an exhibit, adding that the case had been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department, CID, Awka, for discreet investigation. Vanguard News Nigeria. By Vincent Ujumadu A 34-year old man, Mr Ifeanyi Apusiobi from Ogbunike in Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra State reportedly ran amok yesterday and killed his two children with a pestle and used the same object to inflict injuries on his 72 –year old father. Anambra State Police Public… June 21, 2020 In "Metro" LANDLORDS and residents of New City Atoji Housing Estate, Nkwelle Ezunaka, Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra State have accused the police of shielding killers of their security man, Mr. Friday Attah, who was killed on Thursday 19 July 2018 while his colleague, Mr. Uche Kalu badly injured. August 22, 2018 In "News" Kinsmen of wife of Governor Willie Obiano, in Ogbunike, Oyi Local Government Area, Anambra State, have sent a distress call to the Acting Inspector General of Police, IGP, Mr. Muhammed Abubakar Adamu, over an attempt by the Police in Zone 9 Umuahia Abia State to shield a suspect from facing… May 13, 2019 In "Metro"